item.title: About Me
item.description: About Me # I’m a PhD student at the University of Utah studying programming languages with Ben Greenman. I live in Salt Lake City. I’ve sung with the BYU Men’s Chorus and I play the piano. Other hobbies include swimming and hiking—Utah has some of the most diverse landscape anywhere in the US: from dense forests to barren desert. If you visit, I highly recommend checking out some of the national parks.
